{"article_id":"taKQCEpKzt3v5XDJ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Republicans voted on a plan","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"to delay the Affordable Care Act for one year ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"raising the prospects of an Oct. 1 government shutdown .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"Senate Democrats and President Obama oppose any attempt","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"to dismantle the law","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"The government will shutdown on Tuesday","depth":3},{"id":6,"text":"if no stopgap spending bill is enacted","depth":3},{"id":7,"text":"WASHINGTON -","depth":3},{"id":8,"text":"Congress moved the nation closer to a government shutdown on Tuesday","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"as House Republicans voted early Sunday 231-192 to advance a stopgap spending measure","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"to delay implementation of President Obama 's health care law for one year .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"`` We will do our job","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"and send this bill over ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"and then it 's up to the Senate to pass it","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"and stop a government shutdown , ''","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"House GOP leaders said in a joint statement .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"The House voted just past midnight ET to send the bill back to the Senate","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"following a day of vigorous debate over the Affordable Care Act ,","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"which begins open enrollment on Tuesday .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"House Minority Whip Steny Hoyer , D-Md. , countered","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"that the public had litigated the health care law in 2012 with the re-election of Obama","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"and accused Republicans of `` rampant irresponsibility ''","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"that increased the prospects of an Oct. 1 shutdown .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"`` By the way , we won this debate in the election , ''","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"Hoyer said on the House floor ,","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"`` But","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"( Republicans )","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"refuse to accept the results of the election . ''","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"The House also voted 248-174 to repeal a 2.3 % tax on medical devices","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"enacted","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"to help pay for implementation of the law .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"The House then voted unanimously on a separate measure","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"to ensure","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"that the U.S. military continues to get paid","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"if the government shuts down .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Because no annual spending bills have been enacted ,","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"a shutdown would stop the flow of paychecks to troops .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"Members of Congress , however , would continue to be paid","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"if a shutdown occurs .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"CLOSE","depth":3},{"id":40,"text":"The Republican-run House has voted to avoid a partial government shutdown next week","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"but also delay President Barack Obama 's health care law .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"( September 29 )","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"AP","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"But the House GOP amendments","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"affecting the Affordable Care Act","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"face certain defeat in the Senate ,","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"where Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid , D-Nev. , said","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"he will not support any bill","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"that dismantles the law .","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"Obama also said","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"he would veto any such bill in the unlikely event","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"it reaches his desk .","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"In a statement , Reid called the House 's action `` pointless ''","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"and reiterated","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"that the Senate will reject the GOP 's latest version of the stopgap bill .","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"`` After weeks of futile political games from Republicans , we are still at square one :","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"Republicans must decide whether to pass the Senate 's clean","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"( bill ) ,","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"or force a Republican government shutdown , ''","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"Reid said .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"White House spokesman Jay Carney called the plan `` reckless and irresponsible ''","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"and said ,","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"`` Any member of the Republican Party","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"who votes for this bill","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"is voting for a shutdown . ''","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"The House also voted to extend the length of the funding resolution by one month from Nov. 15 to Dec. 15 ,","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"and included a controversial `` conscience clause ''","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"that would delay a requirement under the health care law","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"that employers provide health insurance","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"that covers contraceptives for women .","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"House Republicans expressed confidence","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"that the latest strategy could hold more promise in the Senate than their original effort","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"to defund the health care law .","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"`` I think","depth":15},{"id":75,"text":"there are some senators over there","depth":16},{"id":76,"text":"who may be in cycle","depth":17},{"id":77,"text":"that secretly want a one-year delay","depth":17},{"id":78,"text":"and we just got to find the right mix","depth":15},{"id":79,"text":"that enables them to justify that vote , ''","depth":15},{"id":80,"text":"said Rep. Richard Hudson , R-N.C .","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"However , during Senate votes this week , all 54 Senate Democrats stuck together","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"to strip out language","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"defunding the law .","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"Republicans would need 14 Senate Democrats to break party ranks","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"to side with all 46 Senate Republicans ,","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"and there is no indication","depth":14},{"id":87,"text":"those votes exist .","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"Even if they did ,","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"the president has said","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"he would veto any legislation","depth":15},{"id":91,"text":"to undermine the law .","depth":15},{"id":92,"text":"House Republicans ' maneuvering is unlikely to force the tough political votes on Senate Democrats","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"they are seeking .","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"Reid can use Senate procedures","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"to table the two amendments in one vote ,","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"requiring only a 51-vote majority , on Monday .","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"If that occurs","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"- as expected -","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"the stopgap bill remains in the House ,","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"increasing pressure on Boehner to allow an up-or-down vote on the floor","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"to avoid the shutdown .","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"House Minority Leader Nancy Pelosi , D-Calif. , has said","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"Democrats stand ready to provide votes","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"to help moderate Republicans pass the Senate-passed stopgap bill .","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"However , Boehner would likely lose most of his lawmakers","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"and faces internal party pressures","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"to hold firm against the health care law .","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"Reid warned Republicans","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"that the only way","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"to avoid a shutdown","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"was to approve the Senate bill .","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"`` This is it .","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"Time is gone .","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"Our rules are different than the House , ''","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"he said Friday .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"The Senate is not in session this weekend .","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"`` We 're getting closer to a shutdown ,","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"but","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"if the Senate acts as quick","depth":16},{"id":120,"text":"as it 's capable","depth":16},{"id":121,"text":"we can avoid that .","depth":15},{"id":122,"text":"Let 's see what they send back to us , ''","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"said Rep. Tom Cole , R-Okla. , on Saturday .","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"`` We 're working the process","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"the way","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"we 're supposed to work it . ''","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"Further fueling fears of a shutdown was Reid 's acknowledgment","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"that House and Senate leaders are not communicating .","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"In previous budget clashes , behind-the-scenes negotiations were underway .","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"`` We 've made it very clear","depth":13},{"id":131,"text":"that the only way","depth":15},{"id":132,"text":"to solve this problem","depth":15},{"id":133,"text":"is just accept what we 've done ,","depth":15},{"id":134,"text":"just accept it , ''","depth":15},{"id":135,"text":"he said .","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"Boehner 's office said Friday","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"that they had not heard from Obama all week .","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"Most of the public would not feel the effects of a shutdown immediately .","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"Government operations","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"considered essential ,","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"like mail delivery , air-traffic control and Social Security and Medicare , would continue unabated ,","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"but national parks and museums would close .","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"Certain government employees would not get paid ,","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"but they would receive back pay","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"when the government reopens .","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"A short-term shutdown is unlikely to cause much long-term economic damage","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"unless it drags on longer .","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"House Republicans are also working separately","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"to put together a legislative package","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"tied to an impending vote","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"to raise the debt ceiling , the nation 's borrowing limit ,","depth":15},{"id":152,"text":"that will hit Oct. 17 ,","depth":15},{"id":153,"text":"according to Treasury Secretary Jack Lew .","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"The bill would suspend the debt ceiling through the 2014 elections in exchange for a one-year delay of implementation of the health care law and instructions","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"on how to overhaul the federal tax code","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"without raising additional revenue .","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"The package includes a grab bag of perennially popular GOP legislation","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"that is unpalatable to Democrats ,","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"such as construction of a new oil pipeline from Canada to Texas , and increasing means testing for Medicaid recipients .","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"The package has also divided House Republicans for a number of reasons ,","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"forcing leaders to delay initial plans","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"to vote on the package this weekend .","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"Many lawmakers want to resolve the stopgap spending bill first ,","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"while others are concerned","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"that the package does not include enough long-term deficit reduction .","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"Obama has maintained","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"that he will veto any legislation","depth":10},{"id":168,"text":"that seeks to delay or defund his signature domestic achievement ,","depth":10},{"id":169,"text":"and Democrats have vowed not to negotiate over the debt ceiling .","depth":8},{"id":170,"text":"There is no precedent for a U.S. debt limit default ,","depth":7},{"id":171,"text":"but there is consensus","depth":8},{"id":172,"text":"that it could have sweeping , negative consequences for the U.S. economy .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":345,"left":179,"right":344,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":179,"left":177,"right":178,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":177,"left":175,"right":176,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":175,"left":174,"right":2,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":344,"left":210,"right":343,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":7,"right":209,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":209,"left":198,"right":208,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":198,"left":186,"right":197,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":181,"right":185,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":181,"left":8,"right":180,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":185,"left":184,"right":15,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":184,"left":11,"right":183,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":183,"left":12,"right":182,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":182,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":197,"left":188,"right":196,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent